Subject: [PATCH] squeezelite: use mp3 instead of flac in multi-client sync URL

Music Assistant 2.8.7 hardcodes `fmt=flac` in the multi-client sync URL sent
to grouped slimproto players. Classic Logitech Squeezebox hardware
(Boom / Radio / Touch — original SqueezeOS firmware, MAC-OUI 00:04:20)
does NOT advertise FLAC in its slimproto HELO capability list. MA sends
FLAC anyway. The result: players accept the stream, slimproto STAT frames
advance the position counter, MA shows "playing" — but no audio reaches
the speakers, because the firmware FLAC decoder does not produce usable
PCM at the forced FLAC output format.

Switching the sync-mode output to `fmt=mp3` (which every classic Squeezebox
firmware decodes natively in hardware) restores audio in sync mode.

This is a one-line local workaround until MA upstream honors per-player
`output_codec` setting in the multi-client sync path (currently it only
honors it on the solo playback path).

Patches: music_assistant/providers/squeezelite/player.py

diff --git a/music_assistant/providers/squeezelite/player.py b/music_assistant/providers/squeezelite/player.py
--- a/music_assistant/providers/squeezelite/player.py
+++ b/music_assistant/providers/squeezelite/player.py
@@ -278,7 +278,7 @@
             audio_source=audio_source, audio_format=master_audio_format
         )
         base_url = (
-            f"{self.mass.streams.base_url}/slimproto/multi?player_id={self.player_id}&fmt=flac"
+            f"{self.mass.streams.base_url}/slimproto/multi?player_id={self.player_id}&fmt=mp3"
         )
 
         # Count how many clients will connect
